## Avoid hard coding URL to firmware to allow for easier updates

1. list https://firmware.marburg.freifunk.net/experimental/sysupgrade/
2. parse names like `gluon-ffmr-5-experimental-xiaomi-miwifi-mini-sysupgrade.bin` for version number (or use mtime?)

Check firmware build scripts for naming scheme.

## Serve firmware to router so it doesn't need internet connectivity

1. download firmware if *cache* doesn't exist or is outdated
2. get local IP from Telnet connection
3. start web server
4. build URL for wget

## Compare hash with manifest to verify download

1. get `experimental.manifest`
2. parse
3. look for known filename
4. calculate SHA512

Bad [parsing code][1] exists. Or refer to where the [manifest gets written][2].

## Verify firmware signature

https://github.com/freifunk-gluon/gluon/blob/d2b74b4cf048ecb8706809021332ed3e7c72b2f3/contrib/sigtest.sh

## Offer disaster recovery

1. get stock firmware
2. prepare USB drive

[1]: https://github.com/FreifunkBremen/mirror/blob/master/gluon-manifest.py
[2]: https://github.com/freifunk-gluon/gluon/blob/master/Makefile
